<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/28266234-7jane">7jane</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Depends on if you&apos;re talking about the author&apos;s time, or the time period in which the artists she talks about were in. Author-wise, I&apos;d guess from her<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Depends on if you're talking about the author's time, or the time period in which the artists she talks about were in. Author-wise, I'd guess from her point late in the book when she gets comfort to her loneliness online, the time is circa 2000s. Artist-wise: from Edward Hopper (1920s on) to Josh Harris (ending c.2000).<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
